\c 10
\p
\v 1 The proverbs of Solomon.
\q2 A wise son gives pleasure\f + \ft Piel\f* to a father
\q2 And a foolish son is the grief of his mother.
\q2
\v 2 Treasures of wickedness are of no benefit\f + \ft Hiph.\f*
\q2 But righteousness delivers from death.
\q2
\v 3 The Lord does not allow\f + \ft Hiph.\f* the righteous person to hunger
\q2 But the desire of the wicked he thrusts out.
\q2
\v 4 Poor is the he who works with a lazy hand
\q2 But the hand of the diligent ones gains riches
\q2
\v 5 He who gathers in the summer is a prudent son
\q2 He who is fast asleep in the harvest is a shameful son.
\q2
\v 6 Blessings are on the head of the righteous
\q2 And the mouth of the wicked conceals violence.
\q2
\v 7 The memory of the righteous is blessed
\q2 But the name of the wicked will rot.
\q2
\v 8 The wise of heart receives commands
\q2 But foolish lips are thrust down\f + \ft ruined\f* .
\q2
\v 9 He who walks in integrity walks securely
\q2 But he who twists his ways will be known.
\p
\v 10 He who winks the eye\f + \ft maliciously\f* gives pain
\q2 But foolish lips are thrust down\f + \ft ruined\f* .
